			<p class="first_paragraph">
				What I want to draw your attention to in this scene is the sound of the wind. It’s the most noticeable component of the sound and it’s consistent throughout the scene. It contributes significantly to the sense of atmosphere because it contributes two different sense perceptions in one (though we only hear it, we associate the feeling of blowing wind with the sound). It’s a subtle detail and one that would be drowned out if there were some sort of musical score laid over the scene. But without that distraction, the subtle sound of the breeze makes a significant contribution. 
